Management TeamOperations Team Operating Partners
Andrew M. Bursky – Managing PartnerMr. Bursky has been Managing Partner of Atlas Holdings LLC since its inception in January 2002. From June 1999 to April 2002, Andy was a Co-Managing Partner of Pegasus Capital Advisors, L.P. (“Pegasus”), a private investment partnership with approximately $2 billion of capital under management, focusing on control investments in middle-market companies at points of stress or significant change. Andy joined Pegasus in 1999 after 19 years with Interlaken Capital, Inc. (“Interlaken”), a private equity concern focusing on contrarian style, value-oriented investments in middle-market companies. Andy was a co-founder and the Senior Managing Director of Interlaken. While at Interlaken, Andy was responsible for all investments and business development activities, with a primary focus on industrial manufacturing, business services, financial services and distribution. Andy serves as a Trustee of the Eisenhower Fellowships and Washington University in St. Louis and on the Executive Board of No Labels. In addition, Andy currently serves on the Board of Managers for a number of Atlas portfolio companies. Andy is a graduate of Washington University in St. Louis and Harvard Business School.Timothy J. Fazio – Managing PartnerMr. Fazio has been Managing Partner of Atlas Holdings LLC since its inception in January of 2002. He and Andy have worked closely together for more than 17 years. From June 1999 to January 2002, Tim was Principal and Vice President at Pegasus Capital Advisors, L.P., a private investment partnership with approximately $2 billion of capital under management, focusing on control investments in middle-market companies at points of stress or significant change. Prior to joining Pegasus, Tim was a Vice President at Interlaken Capital, Inc., a private equity concern focusing on contrarian style, value-oriented investments in middle-market companies. Tim currently serves on the Board of Managers for a number of Atlas portfolio companies. Tim is a graduate of the College of Arts and Sciences and the Wharton School of Business at the University of Pennsylvania.Sam G. Astor – PartnerMr. Astor joined Atlas in 2007 and serves as a Partner. Sam has led the formation, financing and oversight of several Atlas portfolio companies and has been involved in the evaluation and analysis of numerous businesses and transaction opportunities. Sam serves on the Board of Managers of Erickson Construction and Novipax. Mr. Astor is a graduate of Wesleyan University.Daniel E. Cromie – PartnerMr. Cromie joined Atlas in 2002 and serves as a Partner. Dan has approximately 12 years of private equity experience, throughout which period he has worked with Andy and Tim. Dan serves on the Board of Managers of Aludium, Bridgewell Resources LLC, Capital Equipment Resources LLC, Erickson Framing Holdings LLC, Phoenix Industrial Services LLC, RedBuilt LLC and Soundview Paper LLC. Prior to joining Atlas, Dan served as a consultant for the Commodity Operations Group of Goldman Sachs in a variety of capacities including as a member of the development team of an integrated fixed income, currency and commodities operations system. Concurrently, Dan toured the country as a professional musician. Prior to his professional music career, Dan was a Senior Analyst at Interlaken. Dan is a graduate of the University of Pennsylvania.Edward J. Fletcher – PartnerMr. Fletcher joined Atlas in 2007 and serves as a Partner. Prior to joining Atlas, Ed served as Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Wood Resources LLC, an Atlas platform company. Before that, Ed was Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of a publicly-traded wireless information and communication services company, where he had oversight and responsibility for all financial aspects of the organization. He began his career in 1993 at Ernst & Young LLP ("E&Y") in the Assurance Advisory Services Practice. Ed serves on the Board of Managers of Banker Steel, Detroit Renewable Energy LLC, Finch Paper Holdings LLC, Merchants Metals LLC, New Wood Resources LLC and Veritas Steel LLC. He is also on the Advisory Board for Twin Rivers Paper Company. Ed is a graduate of Fairfield University and has received professional certifications as a Public Accountant in the State of New York and as a Fraud Examiner.Jacob D. Hudson – PartnerMr. Hudson joined Atlas in 2005 and is a Partner. During his career with Atlas, Jake has led the evaluation and execution of numerous transaction opportunities as well as the formation, financing and oversight of several Atlas portfolio companies. Jake serves on the Board of Managers of Atlas AGI Holdings LLC, Atlas AGI Holdings (Cayman) LP, ACR II Motus Integrated Technologies Coöperatief U.A., and on the Supervisory Board of AGI Global Holdings Coöperatief U.A. Jake is a graduate of Wesleyan University.Philip E. Schuch – PartnerMr. Schuch joined Atlas in 2003 and serves as a Partner. Prior to joining Atlas, Phil was employed at E&Y for over 14 years and was a principal of the firm's Transaction Support Group, participating in over 100 domestic and foreign due diligence engagements for private equity investor groups and strategic buyers. At E&Y, he had active participation in company financings and significant involvement in fraud/litigation engagements, including numerous projects involving the United States Department of Justice. Phil serves on the Board of Managers of Atlas AGI Holdings (Cayman) LP, AGI Global Holdings Coöperatief U.A., Atlas Capital Resources Coöperatief U.A., Atlas AGI Holdings LLC, ACR II Motus Integrated Technologies Coöperatief U.A., ACR II Aluminium Group Coöperatief U.A., and Twin Rivers Holdings Partners. Phil is a graduate of West Virginia University and a Certified Public Accountant.Jerome E. Lay – PrincipalMr. Lay joined Atlas in 2009 and serves as a Principal. Jerome has participated in the formation, financing and oversight of several Atlas portfolio companies and has led the eval